Title: The transformations of non-abelian gauge fields under translations
Authors: Bernd A. Berg
Comments: References to work by Jackiw and others are added
\\
  I consider infinitesimal translations $x'^{\alpha}=x^{\alpha}+\delta
x^{\alpha}$ and demand that Noether's approach gives a symmetric
energy-momentum tensor as it is required for gravitational sources. This
argument determines the transformations of non-abelian gauge fields under
infinitesimal translations to differ from the usually assumed invariance by the
gauge transformation, $A'^a_{\gamma} (x') - A^a_{\gamma}(x) = \partial_{\gamma}
[ \delta x_{\beta} A^{a \beta}(x)] + C^a_{bc} \delta x_{\beta} A^{c \beta}(x)
A^{b}_{\gamma}(x)$ where the $C^a_{bc}$ are the structure constants of the
gauge group.
